Common.Highlight.Common.Text: Very good views and natural light
High quality fit out and furnature

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
20 storey building constructed in 1989 with highly attractive blue glass facade. Major tenants are Lavan Legal, Technip and Department of State Development. Excellent river views from most levels in the building. Secure EOT facility with 118 bike racks, 170 pin coded lockers, showers and change rooms in the basement, with new facilities installed Q3 2014. Coffee shop in the ground floor lobby. Typical full floor is 1,097 sqm. 

Located on North Western corner of William Street and Mounts Bay Road directly opposite Elizabeth Quay train station.

Available for sub lease until Nov 2027 or new direct lease.

Level 16 - 1,000sqm approx - Sub lease until 30/11/24 or new direct lease. 3-4 carbays. Brand new high quality fitout and furnished. 18WS,22pax meet/training, 2 x16pax board, 7 offices, 4pax office, big staff breakout, games room, hot desks. Excellent views.

Level 17 - 1095sqm approx - Sub lease until 30/11/24 or new direct lease.3-4 carbays. Brand new high quality fitted and furnished space with outstanding views of the river across to South Perth. Kitchen/breakout, 40 sit stand WS, 3 VC rooms, 11 large offices, 10pax meeting, 1 senior office, utilities2-3 smaller team rooms.

Both floors have fantastic views and good natural light.

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: EXCELLENT VIEWS AND HIGH END FITOUT
